	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=4443'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#FF9900;'>Xalmat</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Honored Guest<br>
			
				Posts: 388<br>
				
				Registered: 03-08-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=4443'>







<img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/aku.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=960#M960">1</a> of 40
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1726 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<font color=red><font size=5>How to Properly Rebalance Mages</font></font><br><B>or</B><br><font color=yellow><font size=5>Here's What Makes Other Classes Better Than Mages</font></font><br><br><B>First premise:</B><br>Magicians are an offense oriented class. Their abilities should be the best rains, area effect spells, bolts, and direct damage spells, second only to wizards.<br><br><B>Second premise:</B><br>Magicians are the top pet class. They should be the most capable at keeping their pet alive at all times. No other class should have better pets nor better pet support spells than magicians.<br><br><B>Third premise:</B><br>Magician utility spells are either the best, or not the best. Class abilities should represent this.<br><br><B>Fourth premise:</B><br>No class should be nerfed to rebalance the magician class; instead the magician class should be increased in power with no equal decrease in another class's power.<br><br><B>Fifth premise:</B><br>Spells of higher level should be an increase in damage AND efficiency, and have comparable cast time.<br><br><B><font size=5>Magician vs Druid Direct Damage</font></B><br><br>Nuke comparison with Druids<br><br><pre>Magician                ->      Druid<br>Burst of Flame 3-5              Burst of Flame	3-5<br>Burn 11-14                      Burst of Fire	12-15<br>Shock of Blades 31-35           Ignite	33-37<br>Shock of Flame 91-96            Careless Lightning	94-99<br>Shock of Spires 158-176         Combust	171-182<br>Blaze 276-292                   Firestrike	282-302<br>Shock of Swords 580-600         Starfire	612<br>Char 680-700                    Scoriae	688<br>Shock of Steel 795-825          Breath of Karana	772-812<br>Seeking Flame of Seukor 1024    Wildfire	1024<br>Shock of Fiery Blades 1005      Moonfire	1150<br>Ancient Shock of Sun 1150       Ancient Starfire of Ro	1175<br>Black Steel 360 mana            Summer's Flame	355 mana<br>Sun Vortex 395 mana             Winter's Frost	390 mana<br>Rock of Taelosia 434 mana       Sylvan Fire	430 mana<br>Ancient Chaos Vortex 474 mana   Ancient Chaos Frost	468 mana</pre><br><br>These spells are specifically chosen because they are the most alike to one another. They share, for the most part, the same mana cost and the same cast time/recast time. However, one quick glance will tell you that druid nukes top out at higher damage/mana efficiencies (and often more damage) than magician nukes.<br><br>The first premise states that no other class should have better nukes than us (damage, efficiency, and cast time) except wizards, because of our focused offense. So here's the proposed changes:<br><br><B>Burn</B><br>	from 11 (level 4) - 14 (level 10)<br>	to   11 (level 4) - 15 (level 10)<br><B>Shock of Blades</B><br>	from 31 (level 8) - 35 (level 12)<br>	to   31 (level 8) - 37 (level 14)<br>	or   31 (level 8) - 37 (level 12)<br><B>Shock of Flame</B><br>	from 91 (level 16) - 96 (level 21)<br>	to   91 (level 16) - 99 (level 24)<br>	or   91 (level 16) - 99 (level 21)<br><B>Shock of Spikes</B><br>	from 158 (level 24) - 176 (level 30)<br>	to   158 (level 24) - 182 (level 32)<br>	or   158 (level 24) - 182 (level 30)<br><B>Blaze</B><br>	from 276 (level 34) - 292 (level 38)<br>	to   278 (level 34) - 302 (level 40)<br>	or   276 (level 34) - 302 (level 38)<br><B>Shock of Swords</B><br>	from 580 (level 44) - 600 (level 48)<br>	to   587 (level 44) - 612 (level 49)<br>	or   580 (level 44) - 612 (level 49)<br>	or   580 (level 44) - 612 (level 48)<br><B>Char</B><br>	from 260 mana, 4.5 second cast<br>	to   254 mana, 4.0 second cast<br><B>Shock of Steel</B><br>	from 275 mana<br>	to   254 mana<br><B>Seeking Flame of Seukor</B><br>	from 7 second cast time<br>	to 5.8 second cast time<br><B>Shock of Fiery Blades</B><br>	from 1005 damage, 334 mana, 6.8 second cast time<br>	to   1150 damage, 320 mana, 6.2 second cast time<br><B>Ancient Shock of Sun</B><br>	from 1150 damage, 6 second cast, 2.5 second recast<br>	to   1175 damage, 5.8 second cast, 2.25 second recast<br><B>Black Steel</B><br>	from 360 mana<br>	to   355 mana<br><B>Sun Vortex</B><br>	from 395 mana<br>	to   390 mana<br><B>Rock of Taelosia</B><br>	from 434 mana<br>	to   429 mana<br><B>Ancient Chaos Vortex</B><br>	from 474 mana<br>	to   468 mana<br><br><B><font size=5>Spell Rebalances</font></B><br><br>Premise Five. Ignoring GoD spells and beyond, two spells are in serious need of fixing.<br><br>Wind of the Desert - Upgrade to Scintillation<br>Throughout the magician's career, the line of Point Blank AE spells has had an increase in efficiency, and has stayed relatively the same in terms of cast time and recast time. Wind of the Desert breaks this trend, to the point where Wind of the Desert is an overall DOWNGRADE to Scintillation.<br><br><B>Wind of the Desert - Upgrade of Scintillation</B><br>	from 780 mana, 6 second cast, 12 second recast<br>	to   624 mana, 3 second cast, 6.2 second recast<br><br>Char is the direct damage form of Lava Bolt in terms of efficiency. Its fast cast, meaning it is higher damage per second than Lava Bolt, but also uses more mana per second than Lava Bolt.<br>Burning Sand should be a similar upgrade over Seeking Flame of Seukor (preferably over the rebalanced Shock of Fiery Blades). It should be a primary DD spell to transition between Shock of Fiery Blades and Black Steel/Sun Vortex, due to its fast cast time and comparative mana efficiency to Shock of Fiery Blades<br><br><B>Burning Sand - Upgrade to Char</B><br>	from 950 damage, 350 mana<br>	to   1050 damage, 300 mana<br><br><font size=5><B>Pet Rebalances</B></font><br><br>First and Foremost, the damage upgrades for pet focuses is, by far, inadequate. Pets do not receive even close to the damage increases that damage and mana foci provide, nor do they scale close in terms of overall melee increases.<br><br>Step one is to increase the damage done by focused pets to reflect the scaling of melee and casters.<br><br>There does not exist a pet focus that bridges the gap between Vex Thal mages and Plane of Time mages. This gap should be fixed<br><br>Ward of Xegony should be the standard in which all other pets are compared to. The "Mancy" line of focuses should bridge this gap.<br><br><B>Summoner's Boon</B> (Ornate) - +5 damage, +1 level<br><B>Minion of Darkness</B> (Vex Thal) - +10 damage, +2 levels<br><B>Aeromancy, Pyromancy, Aquamancy, Geomancy</B> (Elemental) - +15 damage, +3 levels<br><B>Minion of Eternity</B> (Time) - +25 damage, +4 levels<br><B>Ritual Summoning</B> (Qvic)- +35 damage, +5 levels<br><B>Minion of Discord</B> (Tacvi) - +45 damage, +6 levels<br><br>Omens of War pets should scale in a similar manner.<br><br>Second is the major imbalance between magician pet heals, and other class pet heals, Beastlords in particular. Going back to the second premise, this imbalance should never have happened. Magicians should always have the best pet heals.<br><br>At the low end of the spectrum, change is less needed, but still necessary. Healing classes and Beastlords do not have a recast time on pet heals, and neither should Magicians. Furthermore, Magician heals should be as mana efficient (if not more) than beastlord heals, and at least as fast cast.<br><br>Magician Pet Heals should be redesigned from the ground up and closely follow the spell circles of nukes, and a significant pet heal upgrade should occur at regular intervals, once every two or three spell circles.<br><br>Here's one example that follows this.<br><br><B>Renew Elements - Level 8</B><br>	From 3 cast, 25 mana<br>	To   2 cast, 18 mana<br><B>Refresh Elements (NEW) - Level 16</B><br>	90 HP @ level 16, +1 every level after, 30 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Renew Summoning - Level 24</B><br>	2.25 recast, 250 hp @ level 24, 300 hp @ level 29, 75 mana, 3.5 cast<br><B>Refresh Summoning - (NEW) Level 34</B><br>	400 HP @ level 34, +10 every level after (cap at 450), 100 mana, 4 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Mend Summoning - Level 44</B><br>	790 HP @ level 44, +10 every level after (cap at 900), 200 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Transon's Elemental Infusion - Level 52</B><br>	From 7.5 recast, 275 mana<br>	To   2.25 recast, 250 mana, 1200 hp @ level 52, 1300 @ level 60<br><B>Transon's Elemental Renewal - Level 60</B><br>	From 7 cast, 7.5 recast, 400 mana<br>	To 2.25 recast, 275 mana, 1450 hp, 5 cast<br><B>Planar Renewal -  Level 64</B><br>	From 7 cast, 7.5 recast, 1200 hp, 300 mana<br>	To 2.25 recast, 5 cast, 2100 HP, 350 mana<br><br>The other proposed change is to rebalance magician pet heals around what Beastlords currently have in terms of efficiency. In all cases, magician pet heals must not have the extreme recast time they currently have.<br><br><B>Renew Elements</B><br>	From 3 cast, 25 mana<br>	To 2 cast, 18 mana<br><B>Renew Summoning</B><br>	From 3.5 cast, 100 mana<br>	To 3 cast, 46 mana<br><B>Refresh Summoning</B><br>	From 338 hp, 200 mana<br>	To   583 hp, 125 mana<br><B>Transon's Elemental Infusion</B><br>	From 556-580hp, 275 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	To   870-950 hp, 200 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Transon's Elemental Renewal</B><br>	From 900 hp, 400 mana, 7 cast, 7.5 recast<br>	To  1250 hp, 300 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Planar Renewal</B><br>	From 1200 hp, 300 mana, 7.5 cast, 7.5 recast<br>	To  2100 hp, 420 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><br>These changes will ensure that magicians have the best pet heals, and will make magicians significantly better at sustaining their pets.<br><br>Third is the matter of pet buffs, specifically the Burnout line versus the pet haste series that Beastlords have. The haste component does not need to be looked at, its the other statistical boosts these buffs provide. In addition, beastlords can augment their pet with a +75 dex proc buff. Somewhere along the way, beastlords overpowered magicians in terms of buffing up the pet. This should be corrected.<br><br><B>Burnout 3</B><br>	from 50 str, 13 ac<br>	to 55 str, 15 ac, 25 atk<br><B>Burnout 4</B><br>	from 60 str, 16 ac<br>	to 30 ac, 40 atk, 75 dex<br><B>Ancient Burnout Blaze</B><br>	to 100 str, 60 ac, 60 atk, 75 dex<br><B>Burnout 5</B><br>	from 80 str, 40 atk, 22 ac<br>	to 115 str, 71 ac, 75 atk, 75 dex<br>	<br><B><font size=5>Damage Shield Rebalancing</font></B><br><br>Damage shields are an odd bunch, but under no circumstances should druids have more efficient, longer lasting, or faster cast damage shields. While magicians have the highest damaging damage shields, druids have, by far, the most mana efficient. This needs to be fixed.<br><br><B>Shield of Flame</B><br>	from 60 mana, 4 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 60 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Inferno Shield</B><br>	from 80 mana, 3.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 80 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Barrier of Combustion</B><br>	from 100 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 100 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Shield of Lava</B><br>	from 120 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 120 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Boon of Immolation (group)</B><br>	from 360 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 300 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Cadeau of Flame</B><br>	from 155 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 150 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Aegis of Ro (group)</B><br>	from 450 mana, 9 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 350 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Flameshield of Ro</B><br>	from 190 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 180 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><B>Maelstrom of Ro (group)</B><br>	from 450 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast<br>	to 380 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast<br><br>These changes to the damage shields will insure, once and for all, that Magicians have the best and most efficient damage shields.<br><br><B><font size=5>Anti-Summoned Direct Damage</font></B><br><br>Despite magicians being the master of summoned pets, magicians are not the master of destroying summoned beings; druids are. This should be corrected immediately.<br><br><B>Ward Summoned</B><br>	From level 12<br>	To level 4<br><B>Expulse Summoned</B><br>	From level 20<br>	To level 12<br><B>Dismiss Summoned</B><br>	From level 29<br>	To level 24<br><B>Expel Summoned</B><br>	From level 39<br>	To level 34<br><B>Banish Summoned</B><br>	From level 49<br>	To level 44<br><B>Exile Summoned</B><br>	From level 56<br>	To level 55<br><br><font size=5>Conclusion</font><br><br>If these changes go into effect, then the magician class will be much more balanced in comparison to other classes, in terms of our focus on damage output and pet power, and the class would much better meet the five premises above.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546>Arch Mage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Mage) (Retired)<br><a href=http://www.eqsummoners.com>EQSummoners - Administrator/Lead Librarian</a>
							</div>
								
