Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=961#M961">2</a> of 40
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1802 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			A most excellent post indeed. Very well thought out.<br><br>You did however miss a few points which I believe are of top importance aswell.<br><br>For a magician to ever be useful as a DPS class on raids, the magician needs to have an agro reducer just like every other DPS focus class in the game has. Rogues have evade, monks have FD, necros have FD, wizards have concussion. These agro reducing abilities allow a DPS focussed class to pile on more damage then they otherwise would be able to do without getting summoned/killed. If a magician does not recieve an agro reducing spell/ability then a great portion of his damage will be capped at the agro limit with no way to effect it. For that reason, since magicians share many abilities with wizards already, I believe it would be reasonable to open up the Concussion quest to both Wizards and Magicians. The only real effect this would have is allowing raiding magicians to step up to the plate as a DPS class.<br><br>In addition Magicians are also the only DPS focussed caster class that does not have any resist adjustments to their spells. Resist adjustments are there to ensure that spells stick more often and do the proper amount of damage. Necros have -100 on a lot of dots and -200 on life taps, wizards have -50 on all draughts and -300 on lures, there is no reason why magicians should be left out of this pattern. Give magicians -30 on some spells and up to -100 on others, this would put them properly in line with the other DPS caster classes. *note* the magicians Mala line is not the same as innate resist adjustments on spells as they stack with eachother and a wizard and necro recieves full benefits of both on a raid or in a group where a shaman or magician is present.<br><br>I believe these two things are just as important as the stuff listed above. I wanted to add them here because I think the original poster has a pretty nice list and some great ideas how to fix it, well here are two more.<br><br>SoE should get this done, and get it done quickly.	
		</td></tr>
