			>
			A solid and well reasoned post, I agree with everything said. That's not to say there isn't more I'd like to add, but everything stated there is a good way to bring the current mage class in line with other classes. The other problems, such as&nbsp;creating a desire for more than one mage on a raid, could be offset in part by the increase in efficiency and damage, but I think would require the creation of a new spell line (or the fixing/rendering unique&nbsp;of an old one).<BR><BR>As an addendum, I've always felt that focus items should accentuate above all the characteristics of the pet that define it's type. The most powerful focus on my water pet would only increase his hp's a fraction, but his backstabs (above all) by huge amounts, and so on for every pet. Force a decision in the use of pets, and give every pet a very distinct feel, accentuated by focuses.
