	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=30727'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>kurtzicus</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 52<br>
				
				Registered: 05-05-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=30727'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=978#M978">12</a> of 40
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1634 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Asking for 5 mana changes like this:</P>
<P><STRONG>Sun Vortex<BR></STRONG>from 395 mana<BR>to 390 mana<BR><B>Rock of Taelosia</B><BR>from 434 mana<BR>to 429 mana<BR><B>Ancient Chaos Vortex</B><BR>from 474 mana<BR>to 468 mana<BR></P>
<P>is silly.&nbsp; </P>
<P>This does virtually nothing to change class balance from a macro perspective, but only nitpicks according to a "strictly-speaking" definition.</P>
<P>=======================</P>
<P>With respect to the Wind of the Desert proposed upgrades, these make sense, but Rytan already responded on the compendium "negative" when asked about this.&nbsp; His reasoning was that he was giving us an AE that we could chain with Scint, and that was the value-add.&nbsp; Furthermore, with mana regen "out of whack"&nbsp;as he put it, he preferred giving less efficient spells - not more efficient. </P>
<P>======================</P>
<P>Pet upgrades should not be addressed in terms of max hit but in terms of scalable max DPS.&nbsp; Wizard spell damage should be looked at along with current and future Mage spell damage in order to determine an average scalable DPS.&nbsp; The goal should be to make our spell plus pet damage AT LEAST equal to the damage a Wizard can do, due to our lack of utility relatively speaking.&nbsp; We're a damage class.</P>
<P>The nominal DPS of our standard pet (Air) should be scaled from our Kunark weapon (The Epic) which routinely does 120 dps on MOBs at and above its level range.&nbsp; Obviously there is a large range of MOB mitigation, both spell and melee, but some standard model should be assumed in order to set pet damage scaling.</P>
<P>Wizards in OOW will routinely be blasting 7 to 9 k crits, with what amounts to an unlimited mana pool.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Magician damage output cannot be allowed to fall back (4 to 6k crits in spells) due to a pet that does not SCALE UP damage output significantly.</P>
<P>PET DPS MUST SCALE TO MATCH THE DIFFERENCE IN NUKE DAMAGE BETWEEN MAGE AND WIZARD.</P>
<P>=====================</P>
<P>Pet Heals need an upgrade, and we were promised a look into this by Rytan on the compendium last Winter.&nbsp;</P>
<P>=====================</P>
<P>If Damage Shields are going to provide significant scalable damage then the DS value needs to be scalable with the current MOB hp.&nbsp;</P>
<P>=====================</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Kurt</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
