			>
			<P>I think it's a nitpick and should be ignored.</P>
<P>We have real issues to promote, and asking for a 5 mana change in spell cost just clouds the issue, especially when so much of the post is writ large, and so much attention is devoted to that one topic.</P>
<P>The fact that so many things have been presented to the devs doesn't close that case.&nbsp; We need to keep promoting the case, hammering at the case, lobbying the case, and the issues we need to lobby are those that we've been trying UNSUCCESSFULLY to drill into their heads for several years now, not 5 mana differences.</P>
<P>We might have actually achieved some traction recently, and I hate to see us obfuscate real priority with thousandth level priority items.&nbsp; I want the devs to focus on what is important.&nbsp; I want us to give them tunnel-vision to the real solutions for the real problems, because they've shown that distractions cause them to make mistakes or forget about us altogether.&nbsp; (Case in point being the promised heal information update on the Compendium.)</P>
<P>Kurt</P>
