		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			i feel it is important to make all those 5 mana changes.  want to know why?  it sets a pattern.  the pattern is the opposite of what it should be.  if they just start changing new stuff and not the old, druids can and will argue in return about the pattern of the older spells and argue that a return to the pattern should be done.   if however, all these small changes are done (and it shouldn't be hard to change a number here and there on each of the spells, they are very basic changes)  then the whole pattern will be changed and the druids won't be able to point and say, "see, look at this pattern that exists, make this new stuff conform to that."  instead the whole structure will be changed from the bottom up and it should set in stone the changes.	
