<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=1023#M1023">20</a> of 40
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1397 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Xalmet wrote:</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>-------------------------------------------------------------------</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Summoner's Boon</STRONG> (Ornate) - +5 damage, +1 level<BR><B>Minion of Darkness</B> (Vex Thal) - +10 damage, +2 levels<BR><B>Aeromancy, Pyromancy, Aquamancy, Geomancy</B> (Elemental) - +15 damage, +3 levels<BR><B>Minion of Eternity</B> (Time) - +25 damage, +4 levels<BR><B>Ritual Summoning</B> (Qvic)- +35 damage, +5 levels<BR><B>Minion of Discord</B> (Tacvi) - +45 damage, +6 levels</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>-------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<P>Rather than have fixed values to the maximum damage for each of the foci I think it would be far better for each focus to add some level of percentage increase to the pets damage dealing capability.</FONT></P>
<P>This would provide scaleability for the different types of pets currently and maintain the scaleability for any new pets added in Omens.</FONT></P>
<P>I'm guessing it would also be easier to implement than a straight + max damage as pets use the standard mob Damage model of DB + (1-20) DI. Simply multiple the DB and DI by the percentage increase and pet melee would scale perfectly irrespective of pet type.</FONT></P>
<P>As for what I'd think would be needed then I think current Ritual Summoning focussed MS4 needs to do 20% more than it currently does this would be a roughly 40% increase over base damage.</FONT></P>
<P>So replicating the list would get for currently implemented Foci (so not the xxxmancy ones)</FONT></P>
<P><STRONG>Summoner's Boon:</STRONG> +10% DB/DI, + 1 level</FONT></P>
<P><STRONG>Minion of Darkness: </STRONG>+20% DB/DI, + 2 levels</FONT></P>
<P><STRONG>Minion of Eternity</STRONG>: + 30% DB/DI, + 3 levels</FONT></P>
<P><STRONG>Ritual Summoning:</STRONG> + 40% DB/DI, + 4 levels</FONT></P>
<P><STRONG>Minion of Discord:</STRONG> + 50% DB/DI + 5 levels</FONT></P>
<P>Seeing as the xxxmancy effects are not implemented I do think it would be a good idea if a further item or 2 had Minion of Darkness on it. These could be placed in GoD zones such as Ferubi/Sewers/Vxed/Tipt etc. Adding Minion of Darkness to the Dagger dropped by Ofossaa the Enlightened would also seem a good move to provide people with an upgrade path between the easily available LDON focus and the Time/Yxtta/Ikkinz focus. </FONT></P>
<DIV><BR></FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kirium<br>Cestus Dei
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
