			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Maybe its me but is there a REASON we only want to ask for our pets to be fixed VIA some item?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Dont get me wrong the pet augment items are a great idea , BUT there not a means to FIX anything they are there as just that an AUGMENT.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Our pets need to be fixed at the baseline from about the 49+ area.&nbsp; Below that they do just fine and the 49 pet is no slouch but above that the BASELINE pet is underpowered to complete its job efectively.&nbsp; Remember your roots guys and girls, yes many of us are 65 now some with hundreds of AA's but dont let that cloud your judgment.&nbsp; The Base line pet needs some fixing not through augments hell what do you think the warriors would have said if SONY had turned round and said to them "ok guys we have added some extra armour and weapons in game for you those will fix you" I think a few expleteivs would have been forthcoming.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>An Augment for us is much akin to an equipment upgrade for them, no use unless you have it.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Many of the more Vocal exponents in these Forums are high end playing Mages that want more Bang for there Buck however helping all mages, fighting for a baseline increase will help us all not just the chosen few.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Please, Please, Please all I ask is that you remember your fellow mages.&nbsp; those struggling to make there way into the hallowed grounds of the 65 club need help as well.&nbsp; they Can't solo, they just dont have the AA power you do.&nbsp; Yes you did all go through it but then is that realy a reason to make everyone go through it all just because you did ?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>ok well guess i am done , just remember Baseline increase help ALL mages , Augment increase only help those lucky enough to get them !</FONT></DIV>	
